08/05/2025,"748.1349(b)(2) - Admission, Service Planning, Discharge","Admission, Service Planning, Discharge",No,08/12/2025,08/29/2025,"I:Admission, Service Planning, Discharge",Low,No,One of the children's service plans reviewed was not signed by the child.,"The Permit Holder submitted a corrective action plan that indicated the following:

As a corrective action moving forward for deficiency standard;748.1349(b)(2) Initial Service Plan- When given to child then child must sign or operation document child's refusal to sign.

The Director will oversee monthly compliance reviews of ISPs to verify that all required components are addressed, with deficiencies corrected immediately. Staff will receive refresher training on service planning standards and documentation procedures to reinforce accuracy and accountability. Corrective measures will be tracked through internal quality assurance logs, and supervisory oversight will ensure corrective action remains ongoing, with immediate re-training for staff found non-compliant. This plan ensures regulatory compliance while prioritizing child safety, individualized treatment, and professional accountability."
