03/15/2025,748.2303(a) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,04/28/2025,05/07/2025,Individual Standards Evaluated,High,Yes,A staff member made threatening remarks towards a child in care.,"I conducted a follow - up inspection at the operation where I discussed the implementation corrective action plan submitted with the Administrator.

The Administrator submitted a corrective action plan indicating the following:

Immediate action was taken to remove the involved staff from their position pending investigation. Support was provided to any affected child to ensure their emotional well-being. To prevent recurrence, all staff will complete mandatory training on positive behavior management, trauma-informed care, and prohibited disciplinary practices within seven days. Each employee will also sign a statement acknowledging the center's zero-tolerance policy regarding corporal punishment. To promote ongoing prevention, monthly staff meetings will include scenario-based training and role-play exercises to reinforce appropriate discipline techniques. Supervisors will also increase the frequency of unannounced observations and child interviews to monitor staff-child interactions."
03/15/2025,748.2101(2) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,04/28/2025,05/07/2025,Individual Standards Evaluated,High,Yes,A staff member left medication to a child in care accessible and walked away leaving the child unsupervised.,"I conducted a follow - up inspection at the operation where I discussed the implementation corrective action plan submitted with the Administrator.

The Administrator submitted a corrective action plan that indicated the following:

all medications were immediately secured in a locked cabinet accessible only to trained and designated staff members. Furthermore, the center's medication storage policy was reviewed and updated to enhance access control procedures. Staff were re-trained on proper medication storage and documentation. To ensure continued compliance, weekly audits of medication storage areas will be conducted. Additionally, the Health Services Coordinator will review the Medication Administration Log on a weekly basis to confirm that storage and administration practices meet all regulatory standards."
03/15/2025,748.507(1) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,04/28/2025,05/07/2025,Individual Standards Evaluated,Medium High,Yes,"A staff member made inappropriate comments to a child in care as well as holding up a vase in a threatening manner. Also, another staff member was allowed to supervise children who may not be able to fulfill the caregiver responsibilities.","I conducted a follow - up inspection at the operation where I discussed the implementation corrective action plan submitted with the Administrator.

The Administrator submitted a corrective action plan indicating the following:

As an immediate response, the involved staff members were removed from their direct care duties pending administrative review. To address the issue systematically, all employees will undergo a refresher training on professional conduct, stress management, and trauma-informed care within ten business days. To support long-term improvement, monthly supervision and coaching sessions will be established to reinforce positive staff behaviors and promote accountability. Additionally, supervisors will conduct random weekly observations to ensure ongoing compliance with professional conduct standards."
